   <titleInfo>
      <title>Letter, John Watkins in Knoxville, Tenn. to John Probert in Pittsfield, Ohio, 1864 January 12</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>In this letter, dated January 12, 1864, from John Watkins in Knoxville, Tenn. to John Probert in Pittsfield, Ohio, Watkins writes of his hopes that the war will be over soon. He further discusses the treatment of prisoners: "and for the ill treatment that our soldiers receive at there hands in Richmond ... retaliate on our prisoners." He mentions also that his regiment has been moved out of Fort Sanders to East Tennessee Institute.</abstract>
